<para>stitches together open twin edges Generated from function <computeroutput>MR::stitchOpenTwinEdges</computeroutput>. Parameter <computeroutput>mesh</computeroutput> can not be null. It is a single object. Parameter <computeroutput>cb</computeroutput> is a single object. Parameter <computeroutput>cb</computeroutput> has a default argument: <computeroutput>{}</computeroutput>, pass a null pointer to use it. Never returns null. Returns an instance allocated on the heap! Must call <computeroutput><ref refid="expected__size__t__std__string_8h_1af793e30cecbea93250c523d6deeaba43" kindref="member">MR_expected_size_t_std_string_Destroy()</ref></computeroutput> to free it when you&apos;re done using it. </para>
